The impacts of global warming on daily life include, but are not limited to, the following:

Climate change: Global warming can result in climate changes such as rising temperatures, altered rainfall patterns, and rising sea levels, which may trigger extreme weather events such as heavy rainfalls, floods, droughts, heatwaves, etc., posing threats to human life and property.

Health: Global warming will have direct and indirect impacts on human health. For instance, heatwaves can lead to heat exhaustion and heatstroke, while air pollution and pollen can exacerbate respiratory problems.
